South Korean household income rose
for a ninth straight quarter from a year earlier as job market
conditions improved.  Average monthly income at households gained 7.3 percent to
3.9 million won ($3,468) in the fourth quarter from a year
earlier after a 6.5 percent gain in the previous three months,
Statistics Korea said in a report today.  Householdsâ€™ monthly spending excluding tax and social
security-related payments increased 3.1 percent to 2.4 million
